&lt;p&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Provide comprehensive executive support to a small group of C-level executives, managing complex calendars, scheduling meetings across time zones, and coordinating travel arrangements end-to-end.&lt;br&gt;• Organize and book business travel, including flights, hotels, ground transportation, and itineraries, ensuring seamless logistics for executives and visiting guests.&lt;br&gt;• Coordinate internal and external meetings, including preparing agendas, taking notes, and following up on action items to keep things moving.&lt;br&gt;• Handle day-to-day administrative operations, including managing POs for conferences and customer-related items such as reservations, entertainment, and event ticketing, NDA workflows including sending, chasing, and filing, and maintaining organized documentation in Google Drive.&lt;br&gt;• Act as a reliable point of contact for cross-functional coordination, supporting executives with ad-hoc requests, vendor communications, and office-related logistics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proven experience in an Executive Assistant or similar administrative role supporting senior leadership.&lt;br&gt;• Excellent written and spoken English communication skills.&lt;br&gt;• A can-do attitude with a proactive and flexible approach, comfortable juggling multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience working in a tech or high-growth company environment.&lt;br&gt;• Familiarity with AI productivity tools.&lt;br&gt;• Experience with procurement processes or legal document workflows such as NDAs.&lt;/p&gt;

